properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A total of 25 to 40 millimetres of rain expected by Friday evening. A low pressure system is bringing rain to Western Quebec areas. This rain will affect Southern and Central Quebec later this evening. The rain will continue on Friday and will be heavy at times. Total amounts slightly higher than 50 millimetres are possible locally. Since spring freshet has not ended in many areas, flooding is possible in the most vulnerable areas. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Rainfall warnings are issued when significant rainfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant rainfall expected tonight. Further rainfall amounts of 10 to 20 mm are possible. Local total amounts of 40 to 50 mm are possible in areas that receive a thunderstorm. The ground, already near saturation, has a lessened ability to absorb further rainfall. Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. The precipitation is from a strong low pressure system which will track over Northeastern Ontario tonight then into Quebec Friday. Showers will taper off Friday afternoon. For information concerning flooding, please consult your local conservation authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry District Office. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Heavy rain possible for the end of the week. A low pressure system from the American Midwest will bring rain late Thursday evening and Friday over Central Quebec. The rain will spread eastward and affect the Upper North Shore Friday and Saturday. Total rainfall amounts of approximately 25 millimetres are expected over these areas. Since spring freshet has not ended in some areas, flooding is possible in the most vulnerable areas. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.
